<title>UK: Kia Motors sets $80 mln convertible bond.</title>
<headline>Kia Motors sets $80 mln convertible bond.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-01-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>The following equity-linked issue has been priced by joint lead managers LG Securities International Ltd and ING Barings.</p>
<p> BORROWER   KIA MOTORS CORP</p>
<p> AMT    $80 MLN	 COUPON     0.25 PCT  MATURITY   *31.DEC.07</p>
<p> TYPE   CONVERTIBLE   ISS PRICE  PAR	 PAY DATE    11.FEB.97</p>
<p> LISTING    LUX	 DENOMS (K) FIVE	YIELD TO PUT 7.02 PCT</p>
<p> CONVERSION PREMIUM 10.30 PCT ON 7 DAYS AVERAGE CLOSING PRICE</p>
<p> CONVERSION PRICE   17.600 KOREAN WON</p>
<p> CONVERSION PERIOD  11.MAR.97-30.NOV.07</p>
<p> DOWNWARD REFIXING  11.FEB.99, 80 PCT FLOOR</p>
<p> NOTES	*NON-CALLABLE FOR ONE YEAR, THEREAFTER DURING FOUR</p>
<p>		YEARS SUBJECT TO A 140 PCT HURDLE, PUT ON 11.FEB.02</p>
<p>		FX RATE KRW/USD=855.0</p>
<p>-- London Newsroom +44 171 542 7718</p>
